Load dataset & Data cleaning

world_data <- read.csv("owid-covid-data.csv")
africa_data <- world_data[world_data$continent == "Africa", ]
africa_data <- africa_data[africa_data$location != "Western Sahara" & africa_data$location != "Saint Helena", ]

Deal with missing values

N <- dim(africa_data)[1]
smooth_total <- function(old_data) {
  new_data <- numeric(N)
  new_data[1] = 0
  for (i in 2:N) {
    new_data[i] = old_data[i]
    if (old_data[i] == 0) {
      if (africa_data$location[i] == africa_data$location[i - 1]) {
        new_data[i] = new_data[i - 1]
      }
    }
  }
  return(new_data)
}

africa_data[is.na(africa_data)] <- 0
africa_data["total_tests_smoothed"] <- smooth_total(africa_data$total_tests)
africa_data["people_vaccinated_smoothed"] <- smooth_total(africa_data$people_vaccinated)
africa_data["people_fully_vaccinated_smoothed"] <- smooth_total(africa_data$people_fully_vaccinated)
africa_data["total_vaccination_smoothed"] <- smooth_total(africa_data$total_vaccinations)
africa_data["total_booster_smoothed"] <- smooth_total(africa_data$total_boosters)

New death number before and after vaccination
Bootstrap
data_before <- temp %>% filter(date <= as.Date("2021-04-01"))
data_before <- data_before %>% select(new_deaths_smoothed)
data_before <- drop_na(data_before)
data_before <- data_before$new_deaths_smoothed
z.1 <- rep(NA,10000)

data_after <- temp %>% filter(date > as.Date("2021-04-01"))
data_after <- data_after %>% select(new_deaths_smoothed)
data_after <- drop_na(data_after)
data_after <- data_after$new_deaths_smoothed

z.1 <- rep(NA,10000)

for (j in 1:10000){
  boot.before <- mean(sample(data_before, length(data_before), replace = T))
  boot.after <- mean(sample(data_after, length(data_after), replace = T))
  z.1[j] <- boot.before - boot.after #the difference
}

Permutation
df <- temp %>% select(date, new_deaths_smoothed)
df$date <- as.Date(df$date, format = "%Y-%m-%d")
df <- df %>%
  mutate(before_or_after = case_when(
    date <= as.Date("2021-04-01") ~ "before",
    date > as.Date("2021-04-01") ~ "after"
  ))
df <- df %>% select(-date)
df <- drop_na(df)

diff_of_means <- function(df){
  agg <- aggregate(new_deaths_smoothed ~ before_or_after, data = df, FUN = mean)
  return(agg$new_deaths_smoothed[1] - agg$new_deaths_smoothed[2])
}

observed_diff <- diff_of_means(df)

permute_sample <- function(){
  df.permute <- df
  df.permute$before_or_after <- sample(df.permute$before_or_after, replace = FALSE)
  return(diff_of_means(df.permute))
}
N <- 10000
permuted_diff <- replicate(N, permute_sample())
p_value <- mean(abs(permuted_diff) >= abs(observed_diff))
p_value
[1] 0

  df.permute$before_or_after <- sample(df.permute$before_or_after, replace = FALSE)
  return(diff_of_means(df.permute))
}
N <- 10000
